Father Józef Witko: I saw Jesus in a white robe
He's a charismatic.
Crowds are drawn to the Holy Masses he celebrates for release and healing.
He was about a dozen years old when inexplicable things began to happen in his life.
Today, through the Franciscan, others experience it.
For Masses celebrated by Fr Witko for release and healing draw crowds
He was once approached by the parents of a 7-month-old child who had a 7.5 mm hole in his heart.
It was supposed to be operated on.
Father Józef Witko prayed over him.
Later that day, the boy was rushed to the hospital for surgery.
Astounded doctors said: "Operation is not needed, the cavity is only 1.5 mm".
My parents were crying for happiness.
After another prayer, the Franciscan hole disappeared completely.
The clergyman began to experience the extraordinary activities of the Creator as a teenager.
In his dreams, purgatory souls came to him asking for help.
I was awake at night and urged to pray for the dead and those who were dying at that moment.
He also experienced the presence of an evil spirit.
And he had a vision of what happens to a man who commits a mortal sin.
"My body started to change.
I lost my human qualities and began to take on the appearance of an animal," he says.
The invisible force lifted him up, he couldn't get his voice out.
He felt he was lost.
Then God showed him salvation.
"Immersed in the waters of the river symbolizing holy baptism, I was freed and returned to human form...", he recounts.
He didn't tell anyone about these strange experiences.
There was a calling in him.
He was 16 when he joined the Franciscans.
In his sermons, he did not just want to talk about Jesus.
He wanted people to experience him alive.
Members of the Charismatic Renewal Community in the Holy Spirit
In the masses for healing celebrated by Father Witko, many people participate, who count on getting rid of the disease.
The clergyman emphasizes, however, that their main purpose is spiritual healing, not bodily healing.
