See if you wash your hands well.
We all know that you need to wash them (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are coming.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands.
Most of us wash them for less!
All it takes is warm water and plain soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
Washing, we rub not only the undersides and the tops of the hand, but also: the tips of the fingers (combined or individually) – rub them with circular movements against the inside of the other hand, the spaces between the fingers (interlace the hands, rubbing the fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb is covered with the other hand and in such an embrace we spin it a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when you cannot wash your hands) you should wipe your hands with a wet handkerchief, and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the washed handles or doors (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open them through a paper towel.
Iran's President Says He Rejected U.S. Talk Proposal, Donald Trump Denies
Tehran did not engage in talks with the U.S. side during the United Nations General Assembly in New York, despite the U.S. offer to lift sanctions, Iranian President Hasan Rouhani said on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the restrictions to be lifted, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hasan Rouhani, the Americans proposed lifting all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiating a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear program and ballistic missile construction program.
Rouhani: Iran will not engage in talks in an atmosphere of maximum pressure
The Iranian president said he did not agree to take up these talks because of the "toxic atmosphere".
He stated that he had met with American diplomats because he had succumbed to the urgings of France, Germany and the United Kingdom.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure".
"And even if we want to negotiate with Americans in a 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be," Rowhani said.
The day before, the Iranian leader said he did not rule out talks with the U.S., and accused the European parties of favoring U.S. sanctions on Iran.
He added that sanctions imposed on Iran after the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear deal "are a prerequisite that does not allow" for dialogue.
If we can lift this precondition and if America can lift sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America," he said.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation during the past week at the UN General Assembly.
Trump: "Iran asked, I said no"
Donald Trump tweeted that he was the one who rejected the Iranian side's request.
"Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course I said no!" tweeted the President of the United States.
Tension with atomic agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tensions between Washington and Tehran in order to somehow save the 2015 Iran deal to which they were signatories.
It stated that in return for lifting economic sanctions, Iran would abandon its nuclear weapons program and the nuclear sector would be put under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the US withdrew from the agreement in May 2015, other signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
So far, nothing has come of it.
Washington is using tactics to exert maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iran's oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive a permit to export the raw material, it will reduce its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
