Max Kolonko Cuts Off KWW Patriotic Revolution Max Kolonko
KWW The Patriotic Revolution of Max Kolonko is the name of the election committee under which the #R Revolution political formation of Mariusz Max Kolonka was to go to the October parliamentary elections.
The revolution directed its proposal especially to young voters with right-wing views.
Before the election, Kolonko announced cooperation with Marek Jakubiak or Paweł Kukiz, however, none of these coalitions occurred, and the KWW Patriotic Revolution of Max Kolonko himself failed to even collect enough signatures to issue lists in any constituency in Poland.
Now Kolonko reported on Twitter that he ended his cooperation with KWW Patriotic Revolution Max Kolonko.
"I will expect the above mentioned KWW to remove my name from the name.
I kindly ask that you do not include me with the aforementioned entity", he added and announced that more information will be provided soon.
It is not yet known whether the journalist will continue his work, or whether this is the end of the #R Revolution formation.
On 4 July, on American Independence Day, journalist Mariusz Max Kolonko, staying in the US, announced the formation of a new political formation - #R Revolution.
In recent years Kolonko has become famous for hosting the Max TV channel on YouTube, where he comments on events in Poland and around the world.
"We've had enough politicians, we've had enough of your stupid games, we've had enough of your amateur governments.
It is time for the authorities in the state to take over the nation and rule for the good of the nation," Kolonko said at the time.
The party's agenda included, among others, issues concerning the judiciary (should be elected in general elections), tax changes (alignment of the tax-free amount for all), war reparations (in the form of military assistance to NATO's eastern flank states, with particular emphasis on Poland), holding a referendum on gun ownership, limiting the number of MPs or introducing single-mandate constituencies.
A few days after the new political formation was announced, Mariusz Max Kolonko began talks with Marek Jakubiak.
At the end of July, Kolonko posted a message on his social media profile suggesting that #R would join forces with the Kukiz'15 movement.
However, none of these coalitions ultimately happened.
UBS: Gold close to equilibrium point
"The euro rate will remain around the 4.35 PLN ceiling in the coming months, accompanied by a weak economic situation in global markets," announced Michael Bolliger of UBS Wealth Management.
"Expectations of maintaining a solid pace of economic growth and stable monetary policy are in favour of stabilising the zloty's quotations at the current ceiling", the specialist assesses in an interview with Bankier.pl.
In his opinion, despite the pronounced inflationary pressure, the Monetary Policy Council will not decide to raise rates in an environment in which the vast majority of central banks soften policy.
"While the zloty is properly valued – the euro quotations should persist in the coming months around the 4.35 PLN ceiling – Polish bonds are not attractive according to him.
Much more profitable yields than Polish securities are offered by bonds from emerging markets," says Michael Bolliger, head of asset allocation to emerging markets in the company of UBS Wealth Management.
According to a specialist, the main threat to the Polish economy is the economic downturn in the world.
"The global slowdown may yet deepen, but there should not be a severe recession, or at most a decline in GDP dynamics slightly below zero," says Michael Bolliger.
"Investors should underestimate the global stocks that may be harmed by the lack of prospects for resolving the U.S.-China trade conflict and other geopolitical risk factors, including Donald Trump's impeachment procedure and Brexit.
Among the stock markets, Europe should behave relatively least," according to the latest letter to investors by UBS Wealth Management's chief executive, Mark Haefele.
"Actions from euro area countries should behave worse than the US because they are more vulnerable in conditions of heightened uncertainty around global trade and fears of slowing down," the document said.
According to Michael Bolliger, after the bull market in the bond markets of the safest countries pushed the German 10-year yields even to minus 0.74%, it is still possible to deepen the decline in profitability.
However, in the long run, the profitability of long-term, and only short-term, securities should no longer fall due to the banks' monetary easing.
The Fed has the largest field for rate cuts, which should lead to a weakening of the US currency over the next few years.
