British MPs voted against a three-day recess in the House of Commons for the Conservative Party's annual programming conference, which the government requested.
289 MPs voted in favour, against – 306.
It is customary for the House of Commons to sit during party conferences, so that MPs do not have to resign from either attending or sitting in parliament.
